[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: State Construction
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 1 in the main recipe. Transforms raw clinical data into a normalized state vector suitable for the RL model.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_feature(value: float, feature_def: dict) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Normalize a raw clinical value to [0, 1] range using the feature's defined bounds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Why normalize? RL algorithms work better when all features are on similar scales.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     A heart rate of 80 and an SpO2 of 95 are both "normal," but without normalization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the model would weight heart rate more heavily simply because it's a larger number.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         value: The raw clinical measurement
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         feature_def: Dict with 'min' and 'max' defining the expected range
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Value scaled to [0, 1], clipped to bounds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     min_val = feature_def["min"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_val = feature_def["max"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Clip to expected range. Values outside bounds are physiologically extreme
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # and we don't want them distorting the normalization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     clipped = max(min_val, min(max_val, value))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Scale to [0, 1]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if max_val == min_val:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return 0.5  # degenerate case, shouldn't happen with real features
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return (clipped - min_val) / (max_val - min_val)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def construct_state_vector(patient_data: dict) -> np.ndarray:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build a normalized state vector from raw patient data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The input is a dictionary of current clinical values keyed by feature name.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Missing values are imputed as the midpoint of the expected range (0.5 after
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     normalization). In production, you'd use more sophisticated imputation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (forward-fill from last known value, or a learned imputation model).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_data: Dict mapping feature names to current values.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                       Example: {"heart_rate": 82, "spo2": 96, "fio2": 40, ...}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         numpy array of shape (NUM_STATE_FEATURES,) with values in [0, 1]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     state = np.zeros(NUM_STATE_FEATURES, dtype=np.float32)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for i, feature_def in enumerate(STATE_FEATURES):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         name = feature_def["name"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if name in patient_data and patient_data[name] is not None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             state[i] = normalize_feature(patient_data[name], feature_def)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Missing value: use midpoint as a neutral imputation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # This is naive. Production systems forward-fill from the last known
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # value and flag the staleness so the model can learn to be uncertain
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # about stale inputs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             state[i] = 0.5
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Safety Filter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 3 in the main recipe. Applies hard clinical constraints that override the RL model's recommendation.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def check_safety_rule(rule: dict, patient_data: dict) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Evaluate a single safety rule against current patient data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         rule: Dict with 'feature', 'operator', and 'value'
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_data: Current clinical values
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         True if the rule is satisfied (action is safe), False if violated
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     feature_name = rule["feature"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     threshold = rule["value"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # If we don't have the data to evaluate this rule, fail safe (block the action).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Better to be conservative than to allow a potentially unsafe action
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # because we're missing information.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if feature_name not in patient_data or patient_data[feature_name] is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Safety rule check: missing data for '%s', blocking action (fail-safe)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             feature_name,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     current_value = patient_data[feature_name]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     operator = rule["operator"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if operator == ">=":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return current_value >= threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif operator == "<=":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return current_value <= threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif operator == ">":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return current_value > threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     elif operator == "<":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return current_value < threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Unknown operator: fail safe
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def apply_safety_filter(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     action_index: int, q_values: np.ndarray, patient_data: dict
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> tuple[int, bool, str]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check if the recommended action passes safety constraints.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     If not, find the best safe alternative.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the critical safety layer. The RL model optimizes expected reward,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     but it can't guarantee constraint satisfaction. This function provides that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     guarantee by vetoing unsafe recommendations and falling back to the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     highest-Q-value action that passes all safety checks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         action_index: The model's recommended action (index into ACTION_SPACE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         q_values: Q-values for all actions (from the model)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_data: Current clinical values for rule evaluation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Tuple of (safe_action_index, was_overridden, override_reason)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     action_name = ACTION_SPACE[action_index]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check if this action has safety rules
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if action_name in SAFETY_RULES:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for rule in SAFETY_RULES[action_name]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if not check_safety_rule(rule, patient_data):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Safety violation. Find the best alternative.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 reason = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     f"Blocked '{action_name}': {rule['feature']} "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     f"must be {rule['operator']} {rule['value']}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 logger.info("Safety override: %s", reason)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Try actions in order of Q-value (best to worst),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # skipping any that also fail safety checks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sorted_actions = np.argsort(q_values)[::-1]  # descending Q-value
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 for alt_index in sorted_actions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     alt_name = ACTION_SPACE[int(alt_index)]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if alt_name == action_name:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         continue  # skip the one we just blocked
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Check if this alternative passes its own safety rules
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     if alt_name in SAFETY_RULES:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         alt_safe = all(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             check_safety_rule(r, patient_data)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             for r in SAFETY_RULES[alt_name]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         if not alt_safe:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                             continue  # this alternative is also unsafe
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     # Found a safe alternative
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     return int(alt_index), True, reason
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # If nothing passes, fall back to "maintain_current" (always safe)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 return 0, True, reason
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # No safety rules for this action, or all rules passed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return action_index, False, ""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Reward Computation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 5 in the main recipe. Defines how outcomes translate into the reward signal the RL agent learns from.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def compute_step_reward(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     prev_state: dict, current_state: dict, action_taken: str
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Compute the intermediate reward for a single time step.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is called at each decision point during an episode. It provides
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the "shaping" signal that guides learning between the sparse terminal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rewards (extubation success/failure). Without step rewards, the agent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     only learns from episode endings, which makes learning very slow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The reward design encodes clinical values:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Time on vent is bad (complications accumulate)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Desaturation is bad (patient is struggling)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Reducing support is good (progress toward independence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         prev_state: Patient data at the previous time step
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         current_state: Patient data at the current time step
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         action_taken: The action that was executed (string from ACTION_SPACE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Float reward value for this time step
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     reward = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Penalty for each hour on the ventilator.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This creates urgency: the agent learns that keeping a patient on the vent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # has a cost, even if nothing bad happens. Without this, the agent might
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # learn an overly conservative "never extubate" policy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     time_step_hours = 4.0  # assuming 4-hour decision intervals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     reward += REWARD_CONFIG["per_hour_on_vent"] * time_step_hours
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Penalty for desaturation events.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # SpO2 below 90 is clinically concerning. This teaches the agent that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # aggressive weaning that causes desaturation is not free.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if current_state.get("spo2") is not None and current_state["spo2"] < 90:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         reward += REWARD_CONFIG["desaturation_penalty"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Reward for making progress (reducing ventilator support).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Only awarded if the patient tolerated the reduction (SpO2 stayed above 92).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     progress_actions = {"reduce_ps_2", "reduce_ps_4", "reduce_fio2_5", "reduce_fio2_10", "reduce_peep_2"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if action_taken in progress_actions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if current_state.get("spo2") is not None and current_state["spo2"] >= 92:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             reward += REWARD_CONFIG["progress_reward"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return reward
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def compute_terminal_reward(episode_outcome: str) -> float:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Compute the terminal reward when an episode ends.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     An episode ends when the patient is extubated (successfully or not),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     transitions to tracheostomy, dies, or is discharged.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         episode_outcome: One of "successful_extubation", "failed_extubation",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                          "tracheostomy", "death"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Float terminal reward
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if episode_outcome in REWARD_CONFIG:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return REWARD_CONFIG[episode_outcome]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.warning("Unknown episode outcome: '%s', returning 0 reward", episode_outcome)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Policy Inference (SageMaker Endpoint)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 2 in the main recipe. Calls the trained RL model to get action recommendations.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m sagemaker_runtime = boto3.client("sagemaker-runtime", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_policy_recommendation(state_vector: np.ndarray) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Call the SageMaker endpoint hosting the trained RL policy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The endpoint runs the trained Q-network: given a state vector, it returns
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Q-values for each possible action. The action with the highest Q-value
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     is the model's recommendation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, the endpoint would be an ml.m5.large or similar instance
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     running the trained model. For this example, we show the API call pattern.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         state_vector: Normalized state array of shape (NUM_STATE_FEATURES,)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with 'action_index', 'action_name', 'q_values', and 'confidence'
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Serialize the state vector as JSON for the endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # SageMaker endpoints accept various content types; JSON is simplest for debugging.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payload = json.dumps({"state": state_vector.tolist()})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = sagemaker_runtime.invoke_endpoint(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         EndpointName=SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ContentType="application/json",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=payload,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Parse the model's response. Expected format:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # {"q_values": [0.12, 0.45, 0.38, ...]}  (one value per action)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = json.loads(response["Body"].read().decode("utf-8"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     q_values = np.array(result["q_values"], dtype=np.float32)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Select the action with the highest Q-value
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     action_index = int(np.argmax(q_values))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Confidence: how much better is the best action vs. the runner-up?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # High confidence means one action clearly dominates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Low confidence means multiple actions look similarly good.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sorted_q = np.sort(q_values)[::-1]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if abs(sorted_q[0]) > 1e-8:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         confidence = (sorted_q[0] - sorted_q[1]) / abs(sorted_q[0])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         confidence = 0.0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "action_index": action_index,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "action_name": ACTION_SPACE[action_index],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "q_values": q_values,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence": float(confidence),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Episode Logging (DynamoDB)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Maps to pseudocode Step 4 in the main recipe. Logs every recommendation and decision for audit and future retraining.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m episode_table = dynamodb.Table(DYNAMODB_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def log_recommendation(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     episode_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timestamp: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     state_vector: np.ndarray,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommendation: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     safety_override: bool,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     override_reason: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Write a recommendation event to the episode log in DynamoDB.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Every recommendation the model makes is logged, whether the clinician
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     follows it or not. This creates the training data for future model iterations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The clinician's actual decision gets appended later (via update_with_clinician_action).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     DynamoDB schema:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         PK: patient_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         SK: episode_id#timestamp
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Attributes: state, recommendation, safety info, model version
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Patient identifier (de-identified in non-production)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         episode_id: Unique ID for this weaning episode
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         timestamp: ISO 8601 timestamp of the recommendation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         state_vector: The state that produced this recommendation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recommendation: Output from get_policy_recommendation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         safety_override: Whether the safety filter changed the recommendation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         override_reason: Why the override happened (empty string if no override)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # DynamoDB requires Decimal for numbers, not float.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is a known boto3 gotcha that will throw TypeError if you forget.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     item = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "patient_id": patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sort_key": f"{episode_id}#{timestamp}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "episode_id": episode_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "timestamp": timestamp,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "state_vector": json.dumps(state_vector.tolist()),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "recommended_action": recommendation["action_name"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "recommended_action_index": recommendation["action_index"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "q_values": json.dumps([float(q) for q in recommendation["q_values"]]),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "confidence": Decimal(str(round(recommendation["confidence"], 4))),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "safety_override": safety_override,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "override_reason": override_reason,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "model_version": "v1.0",  # track which model produced this
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # clinician_action and outcome will be filled in later
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "clinician_action": None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "step_reward": None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     episode_table.put_item(Item=item)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Logged recommendation for patient %s: %s (confidence: %.2f, override: %s)",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recommendation["action_name"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recommendation["confidence"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         safety_override,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Training Data Preparation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This step prepares historical episodes for offline RL training. It transforms logged episodes into the (state, action, reward, next_state, done) tuples that offline RL algorithms consume.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def prepare_training_batch(episodes: list[dict]) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Convert a batch of completed episodes into training data for offline RL.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Each episode is a sequence of (state, action, reward, next_state, done) tuples.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the standard format for batch RL algorithms like Conservative Q-Learning (CQL)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     or Batch-Constrained Q-Learning (BCQ).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The key insight of offline RL: we learn from what clinicians actually did,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     not from what the model would have done. The training data contains the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     clinician's actions and the resulting patient trajectories.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         episodes: List of completed episode dicts, each containing a list of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   time steps with state, action, reward, and outcome info.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with numpy arrays: 'states', 'actions', 'rewards', 'next_states', 'dones'
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     states = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     actions = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rewards = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     next_states = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dones = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for episode in episodes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         steps = episode["steps"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         terminal_reward = compute_terminal_reward(episode["outcome"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for i, step in enumerate(steps):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             state = np.array(step["state_vector"], dtype=np.float32)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             action = ACTION_SPACE.index(step["clinician_action"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             is_terminal = (i == len(steps) - 1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if is_terminal:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 # Last step: add terminal reward
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 reward = step.get("step_reward", 0.0) + terminal_reward
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 next_state = np.zeros_like(state)  # terminal state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 done = True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 reward = step.get("step_reward", 0.0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 next_state = np.array(steps[i + 1]["state_vector"], dtype=np.float32)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 done = False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             states.append(state)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             actions.append(action)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rewards.append(reward)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             next_states.append(next_state)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dones.append(done)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "states": np.array(states, dtype=np.float32),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "actions": np.array(actions, dtype=np.int32),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "rewards": np.array(rewards, dtype=np.float32),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "next_states": np.array(next_states, dtype=np.float32),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "dones": np.array(dones, dtype=np.bool_),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 7: Offline RL Training (Conservative Q-Learning)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This demonstrates the core CQL training loop. In production, this runs as a SageMaker training job. Here we show the algorithm logic so you understand what's happening inside the training container.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def train_cql_policy(training_data: dict, num_iterations: int = 1000) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Train a Conservative Q-Learning (CQL) policy from offline data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     CQL is the standard choice for healthcare offline RL because it's conservative:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     it penalizes Q-values for actions that weren't observed in the training data.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This prevents the learned policy from recommending actions we have no evidence about,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     which is critical in a clinical setting.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The core idea: standard Q-learning can overestimate Q-values for out-of-distribution
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     actions (actions the clinicians never took). CQL adds a regularization term that
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     pushes down Q-values for actions not seen in the data, while pushing up Q-values
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for actions that were actually taken. The result is a policy that stays close to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     observed clinical practice while still finding improvements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is a simplified version. Production CQL uses neural networks for the Q-function,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     target networks for stability, and careful hyperparameter tuning.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         training_data: Output from prepare_training_batch
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         num_iterations: Number of training iterations
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict representing the trained Q-table (state discretization for simplicity)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     states = training_data["states"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     actions = training_data["actions"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rewards = training_data["rewards"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     next_states = training_data["next_states"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dones = training_data["dones"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For this example, we use a tabular Q-function with state discretization.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Production systems use neural network Q-functions (Deep CQL).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The discretization bins each normalized feature into a small number of levels.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     num_bins = 5
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     num_discrete_states = num_bins ** min(NUM_STATE_FEATURES, 4)  # limit for tractability
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     def discretize_state(state: np.ndarray) -> int:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         """Convert continuous state to discrete bin index (simplified)."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Use first 4 features for discretization (SpO2, FiO2, PEEP, PS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         key_indices = [1, 4, 5, 6]  # spo2, fio2, peep, pressure_support
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         bins = np.clip((state[key_indices] * num_bins).astype(int), 0, num_bins - 1)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         index = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for b in bins:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             index = index * num_bins + b
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return index % num_discrete_states
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Initialize Q-table
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     q_table = np.zeros((num_discrete_states, NUM_ACTIONS), dtype=np.float64)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # CQL hyperparameters
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     learning_rate = 0.1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     discount_factor = 0.99
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cql_alpha = 1.0  # CQL regularization strength (higher = more conservative)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Starting CQL training: %d iterations, %d transitions", num_iterations, len(states))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for iteration in range(num_iterations):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Sample a random mini-batch from the training data
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         batch_size = min(64, len(states))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         indices = np.random.choice(len(states), size=batch_size, replace=False)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for idx in indices:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             s = discretize_state(states[idx])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             a = actions[idx]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             r = rewards[idx]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             done = dones[idx]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if done:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 target = r
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ns = discretize_state(next_states[idx])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 target = r + discount_factor * np.max(q_table[ns])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Standard Q-learning update
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             td_error = target - q_table[s, a]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             q_table[s, a] += learning_rate * td_error
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # CQL regularization: push down Q-values for all actions,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # then push up the Q-value for the action actually taken.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Net effect: actions seen in data keep their values,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # unseen actions get penalized.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             q_table[s] -= learning_rate * cql_alpha * (q_table[s] - q_table[s].mean())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             q_table[s, a] += learning_rate * cql_alpha * 0.5
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if (iteration + 1) % 200 == 0:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             mean_q = q_table[q_table != 0].mean() if np.any(q_table != 0) else 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             logger.info("  Iteration %d/%d, mean Q-value: %.3f", iteration + 1, num_iterations, mean_q)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("CQL training complete.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"q_table": q_table, "num_bins": num_bins, "discretize_fn": discretize_state}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full inference pipeline assembled into a single function. This is what runs when a new patient state arrives and the system needs to produce a recommendation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def generate_weaning_recommendation(patient_id: str, patient_data: dict, episode_id: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full ventilator weaning RL pipeline for one decision point.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the main entry point for real-time inference. It takes the current
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient state, runs it through the RL model, applies safety constraints,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and logs the recommendation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id: Patient identifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_data: Dict of current clinical values (raw, unnormalized)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                       Example: {"heart_rate": 82, "spo2": 96, "fio2": 40, ...}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         episode_id: Unique ID for this weaning episode
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with the final recommendation, safety info, and confidence
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timestamp = time.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ", time.gmtime())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Construct normalized state vector from raw clinical data
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[1/4] Constructing state vector for patient {patient_id}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     state_vector = construct_state_vector(patient_data)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"       State vector: {state_vector.shape[0]} features, "
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m           f"mean={state_vector.mean():.3f}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 2: Get RL model recommendation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"[2/4] Querying RL policy endpoint: {SAGEMAKER_ENDPOINT}")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recommendation = get_policy_recommendation(state_vector)
